  "text": "The transition between these two extremities is realised by several quasi-linear PV relationships, the slope of which is given by the activation function, also named the driver function, e(t) : With the number of Gaussians N = 1, the magnitude A 1 = 1, the width B 1 = 80s -2 , the delay C 1 = 0.27 s and the duration of a cardiac cycle D 1 = 1s, as defined in Smith et al. [CITATION_1] . Heart rate (HR beats/min) does not appear explicitly, but it is used to determine the value of one diver function parameter, D 1 = 60/HR. This model doesn't use ECG data, but information relative to timing, delay and duration of the ventricular contraction is contained in the driver function parameters. This activation function accounts for myocardial activation and drives the changes in elastance. It varies between 0 and 1. Then, the pressure in the ventricle at any time t of a cardiac cycle is linked to the volume by:",
