      "span_text": "The transition between these two extremities is realised by several quasi-linear PV relationships, the slope of which is given by the activation function, also named the driver function, e(t) : With the number of Gaussians N = 1, the magnitude A 1 = 1, the width B 1 = 80s -2 , the delay C 1 = 0.27 s and the duration of a cardiac cycle D 1 = 1s, as defined in Smith et al.  ."
